1
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:18,670
Wow. We have gone from winter to summer immediately. And I'm actually thankful for that. It's good to finally let the boys go out and play in the water, outside, please.

2
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:28,460
It's been a good weekend. I trust you had a wonderful, safe, and sane holiday, and that you are continuing to enjoy this patriotic weekend.

3
00:00:29,660 --> 00:00:31,380
I'd like to begin just with this idea.

4
00:00:32,660 --> 00:00:35,800
A father was talking with a rather rebellious son,

5
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:42,420
and he said, every person who lives in these United States is a privileged person.

6
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,280
And the boy answered, well, I disagree.

7
00:00:46,490 --> 00:00:49,570
And the father replied, that's the privilege.

8
00:00:50,010 --> 00:00:51,920
We can disagree.

9
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:55,410
We have the privilege to speak our mind.

10
00:00:55,990 --> 00:01:00,090
We have freedom of religion, freedom to speak, freedom of the press,

11
00:01:00,090 --> 00:01:07,820
freedom to pursue hopes and dreams we are free in this nation in so many ways

12
00:01:07,820 --> 00:01:14,640
we have these rights because of what our forefathers and mothers did a long time ago

13
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:22,460
you and i didn't earn the privileges that we enjoy as citizens of this land a poet said this

14
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:30,520
and very well we eat from orchards we did not plant we drink from wells we did not dig

15
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:34,240
We reap from fields we did not sow.

16
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,520
We are warmed by fires we did not kindle.

17
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:41,640
We are sheltered by roofs that we did not build.

18
00:01:42,220 --> 00:01:44,900
And we're blessed by monies we did not give.

19
00:01:46,010 --> 00:01:51,090
Friends, we are in a very blessed situation, a very blessed land, a very blessed people,

20
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:54,750
a free people, thank the Lord.

21
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:59,990
A lot of symbols of freedom that we've been seeing throughout the weekend.

22
00:01:59,990 --> 00:02:03,550
there are some other symbols that you might not be aware of

23
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:05,310
I'd like to bring to your attention

24
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:09,820
for one, the Alamo in Texas stands

25
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:11,880
as a symbol of freedom

26
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:17,120
in Israel, a mountaintop experience

27
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,600
a place called Masada

28
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:22,710
where years and years ago

29
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:26,110
960 men and women defied the Roman government

30
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:29,190
as a symbol to them of freedom

31
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:39,850
Believe it or not, in Afghanistan today, the presence or absence of hair is a symbol of freedom.

32
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:43,560
Men shave their beards, women uncover their hair.

33
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:47,880
To them, those are symbols of great freedom that they now possess.

34
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:56,580
In Berlin, the symbol is the absence of the wall.

35
00:02:56,580 --> 00:03:02,360
The absence of a dividing wall that has divided that city for years

36
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:05,140
Is a symbol of freedom

37
00:03:05,140 --> 00:03:11,430
And in our country today, the flag, the liberty bell, the Statue of Liberty, the eagle

38
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:15,590
Are symbols that we recognize, that point to freedom

39
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:19,240
We take pride in those symbols

40
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,580
We take pride in the events that led to our freedom

41
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:25,000
We take pride in the symbols of our liberty

42
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:31,060
We take pride in the reality of our religious and political and personal freedom.

43
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:38,580
But with all those symbols, for all those symbols of freedom throughout the world,

44
00:03:38,580 --> 00:03:50,060
there is one symbol that stands far above the rest, far above a flag or a bell, a mountaintop or a wall.

45
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:56,060
A symbol of freedom is the cross of Jesus Christ.

46
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,980
That is the ultimate symbol of freedom

47
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:05,880
for peoples in this land and in lands around the globe.

48
00:04:07,810 --> 00:04:12,050
It's the symbol of freedom from sin, from death.

49
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:15,470
It represents the ultimate sacrifice by God

50
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:17,790
to free us for eternity.

51
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:21,730
I share with you Romans chapter 6.

52
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:25,180
Beginning verse 17, Paul writes,

53
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:36,520
Thank God, once you were slaves of sin, but now you have obeyed with all your heart the new teaching God has given you.

54
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:45,420
Now you are free from sin, your old master, and you have become slaves to your new master, righteousness.

55
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:53,660
I speak this way using illustration of slaves and masters because it's easy to understand.

56
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:59,800
Before, you let yourselves be slaves of impurity and lawlessness.

57
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:05,960
Now you must choose to be slaves of righteousness, so that you will become holy.

58
00:05:06,990 --> 00:05:11,890
In those days when you were slaves of sin, you weren't concerned with doing what was right.

59
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:15,370
And what was the result? It was not good.

60
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:22,090
Since now you are ashamed of the things you used to do, things that end in eternal doom.

61
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:26,080
but now you are free from the power of sin

62
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:28,580
and have become slaves of God.

63
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,340
Now you do those things that lead to holiness

64
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:35,000
that result in eternal life

65
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,660
for the wages of sin is death

66
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:42,460
but the free gift of God is eternal life

67
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:45,440
through Jesus Christ our Lord.

68
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:50,450
That is worthy of an amen in our hearts.

69
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,240
Amen.

70
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:56,140
We're finishing our series of kingdom living.

71
00:05:57,340 --> 00:06:04,120
And now we're seeing how this dimension of our faith, our freedom, what it really looks like, how we can experience it.

72
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:06,860
Many think today they are free.

73
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:10,540
After all, the symbols of our land point to our freedom.

74
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,580
And at one level, we are free.

75
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,360
We're free to travel.

76
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:16,660
We're free to pursue happiness.

77
00:06:16,660 --> 00:06:19,420
We're free to believe what we want.

78
00:06:22,060 --> 00:06:24,340
But there's a freedom that's deeper than that.

79
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:33,420
A freedom that's freedom from our sin, freedom from our broken nature, freedom from our sickness in our souls,

80
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:38,480
freedom from the torment of spiritual beings in the spiritual realm.

81
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:41,440
There's freedom, friends, this morning.

82
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,880
Our culture doesn't talk about sin much today.

83
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:51,700
In fact, the whole idea of sin the world thinks is cute or passe.

84
00:06:52,420 --> 00:06:55,850
We don't want to acknowledge that there are boundaries.

85
00:06:55,850 --> 00:07:00,470
We don't like the idea of limits to freedom.

86
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,530
But friends, in the spiritual realm, there are boundaries.

87
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:06,650
There are ultimate rights and wrongs.

88
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:12,040
In fact, in the evangelical church, we don't talk about the spiritual realm much at all.

89
00:07:15,090 --> 00:07:20,290
But there are forces in the spiritual realm that also oppress and torment.

90
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:22,430
And Jesus knew about it and dealt with it.

91
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:24,030
He knew those realities were there.

92
00:07:24,030 --> 00:07:30,880
And he proclaimed freedom for those who were in him from those realities.

93
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:36,430
And regarding sin, sin is tricky.

94
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:43,900
Sin is something that can ensnare us and we become unaware of our own bondage.

95
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,660
We think we're free, but we're not.

96
00:07:49,530 --> 00:07:54,090
And when we're in bondage, we are good at minimizing our enslavement.

97
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:58,650
We think, well, a few more adjustments, a little more of this, a little more of that,

98
00:07:58,690 --> 00:08:00,830
and everything's going to be fine, but it's not true.

99
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,100
What's true is that evil can become a habit,

100
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:10,060
and a habit that's hard to break, and it becomes an enslaving experience.

101
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:16,640
We can be a slave to hatred or hostility, rage.

102
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,540
We can be enslaved to those experiences.

103
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:21,380
We can be a slave to our pride.

104
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:26,510
In our arrogance, we can indulge in prejudice and bigotry

105
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:29,210
because we think we're better than others.

106
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:32,590
In our self-importance,

107
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:34,990
we enjoy telling somebody when they're wrong

108
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:36,630
to elevate ourselves.

109
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:39,900
We can be a slave to gossip.

110
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:43,510
We can be a slave to the misuse of our sexuality.

111
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:47,960
We can be a slave to relationships that damage us.

112
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,780
Adultery, premarital sex, and so on.

113
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:53,060
We can be a slave to materialism.

114
00:08:54,530 --> 00:08:55,930
We've got to buy one more thing,

115
00:08:56,050 --> 00:08:57,050
and then we'll be satisfied.

116
00:08:57,050 --> 00:09:02,060
Just one more this, one more that, but we're never satisfied.

117
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:09,950
We're enslaved, and all that misuse of freedom is the grip of sin in our lives.

118
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:13,590
It gradually takes root, and it binds us up.

119
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,280
We need a Savior.

120
00:09:19,730 --> 00:09:26,070
We need God Himself to intervene, which is what He did in Jesus Christ.

121
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:28,050
Take a look at John chapter 8.

122
00:09:29,260 --> 00:09:31,720
Jesus said to the people who believed in him,

123
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:37,500
You are truly my disciples if you keep obeying my teachings,

124
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:44,030
and you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free.

125
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:49,450
But we are descendants of Abraham, they said.

126
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:53,030
We've never been slaves to anyone on earth.

127
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:55,570
What do you mean, set free?

128
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:57,930
And Jesus replied,

129
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:02,610
I assure you that everyone who sins is a slave of sin.

130
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:05,410
A slave is not a permanent member of the family,

131
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:09,070
but a son is part of the family forever.

132
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:12,480
So if the Son sets you free,

133
00:10:13,110 --> 00:10:16,010
you will indeed be free.

134
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,570
Praise the Lord for that.

135
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:21,910
Freedom in Christ.

136
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:23,670
I'd like to share three points with you.

137
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,010
Bruce Milne helped me with this.

138
00:10:25,070 --> 00:10:26,250
Great theologian and pastor.

139
00:10:26,930 --> 00:10:28,710
Very great insight on this passage.

140
00:10:29,210 --> 00:10:33,120
Freedom in Christ, number one, is a gift.

141
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,060
It's a gift.

142
00:10:37,230 --> 00:10:40,530
Freedom in Christ does not come from our background.

143
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:44,850
It doesn't come from our nationality, come from our pedigree.

144
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:46,090
It's a gift.

145
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:54,140
Freedom in Christ is given personally by Jesus himself to us.

146
00:10:56,620 --> 00:11:00,860
In this narrative, the Jews thought that their history,

147
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:05,920
their nationality qualified them to be implicitly part of God's plan.

148
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:08,000
And they weren't slaves of anyone.

149
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:14,920
But Jesus says, if you disobey God, you're already a slave of your broken nature.

150
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,340
You already are a slave of sin.

151
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,960
And you need a Savior.

152
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:26,450
And Jesus gives that gift to us, to anyone that receives it.

153
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:29,560
A freedom from ourselves.

154
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:31,710
It's freedom in Christ.

155
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,660
The second point I would like just to point out is that it's eternal.

156
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:43,520
When you accept Jesus Christ as the Lord, the director, the leader of your life,

157
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:48,160
when you accept what he did on the cross, you become a child of God.

158
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:50,830
And you're part of God's family.

159
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:56,270
And when you're part of God's family, as Jesus lives forever, so shall you.

160
00:11:56,270 --> 00:12:00,790
and you're free from yourself, from your sin, from your torment forever.

161
00:12:02,050 --> 00:12:06,990
I can't think of a better gift than to have freedom now and forever.

162
00:12:09,190 --> 00:12:10,330
Oh, it's great news.

163
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,280
It's great news.

164
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:15,220
Fourth of July is good news for our country,

165
00:12:15,220 --> 00:12:20,290
but this news is even better, even better.

166
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:29,430
Freedom in Christ finally is expressed in obedience.

167
00:12:29,430 --> 00:12:34,960
I love what the great church reformer

168
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,920
Martin Luther said and taught

169
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:39,830
he taught and I believe he's right

170
00:12:39,830 --> 00:12:43,850
that human beings were made to serve

171
00:12:43,850 --> 00:12:47,770
we were not made to just have unbridled freedom

172
00:12:47,770 --> 00:12:50,290
we were made to serve

173
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:53,880
he described it this way

174
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:57,730
the human will he described it

175
00:12:57,730 --> 00:12:59,610
is like a horse

176
00:12:59,610 --> 00:13:02,740
and we have a choice

177
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,100
who's going to ride

178
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:07,600
Either the Lord or the enemy himself.

179
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,160
That's it.

180
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:10,380
Two choices.

181
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:14,200
God is riding this horse or the devil is riding this horse.

182
00:13:14,420 --> 00:13:17,740
But we're going to have somebody control us.

183
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,760
We're going to serve somebody.

184
00:13:21,170 --> 00:13:24,370
And if we're serving ourselves, we're serving the enemy anyway.

185
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:28,600
We were built, though, created to serve.

186
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:33,160
The question is, who are we serving?

187
00:13:33,260 --> 00:13:35,700
Are we serving sin or God?

188
00:13:37,180 --> 00:13:42,500
Our freedom in Christ that Jesus gives us frees us to serve God.

189
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:48,080
And when you serve God, then you find what you were made for, created for.

190
00:13:48,540 --> 00:13:49,760
Pieces fit together.

191
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:56,050
You find great joy and peace in serving God.

192
00:13:56,350 --> 00:14:05,570
This whole idea in our country and contemporary philosophy that to be totally radically free,

193
00:14:05,570 --> 00:14:08,670
to be free of any constraints

194
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:10,070
that somehow that's freedom.

195
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:11,710
Friends, that's not freedom.

196
00:14:12,190 --> 00:14:13,050
That's lost.

197
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:17,110
We're created to serve God.

198
00:14:20,380 --> 00:14:23,160
Freedom is not the freedom to do as we want,

199
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:28,240
but the freedom from being controlled by our sin

200
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,060
that will then enslave us.

201
00:14:30,180 --> 00:14:32,620
Real freedom is freedom in Christ to serve God.

202
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:37,040
When you receive God's freedom,

203
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:42,210
you become a loving, obedient child in His family.

204
00:14:42,390 --> 00:14:47,820
And when we're obedient children in His family,

205
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:51,180
when we do what Jesus our Master says to do,

206
00:14:51,180 --> 00:14:54,780
we take into our hearts and actions His Word to us.

207
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:58,000
We experience His power in our lives.

208
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:03,220
And that experience and knowledge of God sets us free.

209
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,180
And then we're free to serve God more fully.

210
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,120
And serving Christ is true freedom.

211
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,080
Don't stop.

212
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:18,380
My encouragement to you is don't stop taking in God's Word.

213
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,680
Don't stop being obedient to Jesus.

214
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:23,960
Don't stop allowing the Spirit of God to fill you up

215
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:29,340
that you might be serving the Lord where true freedom is found.

216
00:15:29,420 --> 00:15:30,120
Don't stop.

217
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:35,090
A little boy was watching his mother in the bathroom,

218
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,720
and she was gently rubbing cold cream on her face.

219
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:44,680
And he said, Mommy, why are you rubbing that cream on your face?

220
00:15:45,020 --> 00:15:45,600
He asked.

221
00:15:46,530 --> 00:15:50,130
And she said, To be more beautiful, said his mom.

222
00:15:50,130 --> 00:15:59,530
and a few minutes later she starts taking it off and he said what's the matter are you giving up

223
00:15:59,530 --> 00:16:14,500
jesus doesn't want us to give up he wants us to walk in obedience each and every day

224
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:21,570
with the power of the spirit flowing in our lives and as we serve in our obedient we'll find

225
00:16:21,570 --> 00:16:28,160
freedom to do more than what god calls us to do to have more boldness to serve him to have more

226
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:36,730
power to live in freedom in Christ. Friends, when you're obedient to Christ, when you don't give up,

227
00:16:36,790 --> 00:16:43,610
when you step each and every day, one foot in front of the other, you're free to love instead

228
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:57,560
of hate. You find freedom to be joyous in the midst of sorrow. You'll find freedom to have peace

229
00:16:57,560 --> 00:17:08,560
even in the midst of conflict you'll be free to wait with god when others might be moved by

230
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:20,920
circumstance you're free to listen to god you find yourself free to be kind when others hurt

231
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:32,590
when others hurt you you find freedom to do good when others do evil you have freedom to have

232
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:40,850
Christ be your anchor when others have nothing to trust in nothing to believe in nothing to root

233
00:17:40,850 --> 00:17:49,730
their lives you have the freedom to have the God of the universe as your anchor you have freedom

234
00:17:49,730 --> 00:17:59,320
to let Christ lead you in daily steps of righteousness and holiness you have freedom

235
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:10,440
from yourself from wrongful passions and desires that's good news we're free to rise above our sin

236
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:15,860
we're free to live a holy life we're free to finally choose right we're free to choose the

237
00:18:15,860 --> 00:18:22,880
best we're free to keep on growing we're free to reach the potential for which god has designed us

238
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:32,270
that's the freedom we receive in christ does that warm your hearts this morning i hope so

239
00:18:32,270 --> 00:18:39,950
it gets me all excited to think about all those benefits of knowing christ i love my freedom in

240
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:46,540
this country but even in the midst of political tyranny we still can enjoy these freedoms that's

241
00:18:46,540 --> 00:18:51,940
why the church of jesus christ flourishes even under persecution because the freedom in christ

242
00:18:51,940 --> 00:19:00,500
